Condition : 7 - Prior to commencement of development, a Construction Management an  Logistics Plan shall be submitted to an approved by the Local Planning Authority. The development shall take place in accordance with the details approved. The plan shall accord to the latest Transport for London Guidance and contain the following details:
o	A site plan;
o	A pre-start record of site condition on the adjoining public highway to be agreed with the Council;
o	Provision for the parking of vehicles of site operatives and visitors; 
o	Provision for loading and unloading of plant and materials used in constructing the development; 
o	Provision for the storage of plan and materials used in constructing the development;
o	The erection and maintenance of security hoarding including decorative displays and facilities for public viewing, where appropriate; 
o	Wheel washing facilities at the site exit; 
o	Measures to control the emission of dust and dirt during construction; 
o	Details of any lighting including location within the site and specification;
o	A scheme for recycling/ disposing of waste resulting from demolition and construction works; 
o	Appropriate vehicle routes to and from the site; 
o	Measures to ensure the safety of all users of the public highway especially in the vicinity of the site; 
o	Use of operators committed to best practice, demonstrated by membership of TFL's Freight Operator Recognition Scheme, or similar; 
o	Measures to promote sustainable travel to work; and
o	Swept path analysis for HGV's including dustcarts.

Condition : 20 - Notwithstanding the approved plans and documents, prior to commencement of works excluding site investigations, an Ecology Report to assess any potential ecological impacts on the neighbouring SINC prepared by a suitably qualified ecologist (CIEEM and BSI) including details of any required mitigation measures, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.
The report shall cover:
i.	The impacts of the proposed development on the Longford River SINC: 
a.	risk of dust and other contamination during works;
b.	Potential increase in artificial lighting and impacts on bats and other wildlife given development immediately adjacent to the river corridor, taking account of any mitigation provided by tree retention;
ii.	Protected and/or notable species within the site, including potential for bat roosts and bird nesting within any existing buildings, given the proximity of the site to the Longford River habitat corridor and SINC;
iii.	Any mitigation methods to be incorporated within the proposal and construction methods/programme;
iv.	The provision of bat/bird nesting features and provision of green roofs on the completed building(s) and associated structures.
The development shall thereafter be completed in accordance with the approved details, including the implementation of any mitigation measures required, and maintained as such thereafter.
